\section{Interpolation}{

Each analyte is interpolated independently:
\itemize{
\item \code{"forward_fill"} carries the last directly observed value forward
until the next grab.  Produces a step function.
\item \code{"linear"} linearly interpolates between consecutive observations.
For SSD-eligible toxicants (metals, ammonia), interpolation is performed
in log-concentration space, which is more appropriate for log-normally
distributed data and avoids negative intermediate values.  Co-analytes
(pH, temperature, DOC, hardness) are interpolated linearly.
\item \code{"model"} fits a season-blind \code{\link[=fit_target_model]{fit_target_model()}} on the grab
chemistry and the supplied \code{reference_model}, and predicts each
toxicant's concentration between grabs as
\code{reference + impact}, where the impact (the leachate-attributable
increment) is modelled from hydrology and a persistent latent state but
\strong{never} from day-of-year. Co-analytes are forward-filled. Requires
\code{reference_model}; see \code{\link[=fit_target_model]{fit_target_model()}} for the method.
}
Below-detection values are treated as their detection-limit value for
interpolation purposes, matching the treatment in \code{\link[=add_amspaf]{add_amspaf()}}.
}

\section{Leading edge}{

Days before the first grab sample for an analyte are outside the observation
record:
\itemize{
\item \code{"drop"} (default) excludes such days from the output.
\item \code{"backfill"} assigns the first observed value to all earlier days.
Use cautiously -- it assumes the analyte was at its first observed level
before sampling commenced.
}
}

\section{Temperature for ammonia}{

When \code{NH3-N} is in \code{df}, water temperature is required per sample for the
un-ionised fraction normalisation.  Two sources are accepted:
\itemize{
\item Temperature rows already in \code{df} (measured on grab-sample days) are
interpolated along with other analytes.
\item An external daily temperature series supplied via the \code{temperature}
argument (e.g. from \code{\link[=estimate_water_temp]{estimate_water_temp()}}) fills in days without a
grab temperature.  Grab-sample-day measurements take priority.
}
Set \code{require_temperature = FALSE} only for datasets that do not contain
ammonia.
}

